            ],
            "params": [],
            "parts": [
              {
                "id": "SV-243238r856613_rule_statement",
                "name": "statement",
                "prose": "The network device must not be configured to have any feature enabled that calls home to the vendor."
              },
              {
                "id": "SV-243238r856613_rule_guidance",
                "name": "guidance",
                "prose": "Configure the network device to disable the call home service or feature.\n\nNote: This feature can be enabled if the communication is only to a server residing in the local area network or enclave."
              },
              {
                "id": "SV-243238r856613_rule_vulnerability-discussion",
                "name": "vulnerability-discussion",
                "prose": "Call-home services will routinely send data such as configuration and diagnostic information to the vendor for routine or emergency analysis and troubleshooting. There is a risk that transmission of sensitive data sent to unauthorized persons could result in data loss or downtime due to an attack. (See SRG-NET-000131-RTR-000083.)"
